n opportunity for reassessment, particularly in the film's relationship to male prostitution, male relationships, and sexual identity.By shifting the perspective away from previous interpretations of Midnight Cowboy as homophobic and problematic, Towlson argues for a new interpretation of the film as a proto-queer buddy movie and a critical forerunner to films such as My Own Private Idaho and Brokeback Mountain.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGay people in motion pictures. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  a1969.  aDustin.  aForty Second Street.  aHoffman.  aHollywood.  aJames Leo Herlihy.  aJohn Schlesinger.  aJon Voight.  aNew York.  aWaldo Salt.  abuddy.  acinema.  acriticism.  afilm.  ahustlers.  aidentity.  amovie.  aqueer.  asex.  awork.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311127195808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packagez978311143542840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780228017226?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228017226423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228017226/original  a978-3-11-127195-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-143542-8  ACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packageb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles